fr:mainmatter.fr:p:
An introduction form is a syntactic term that is constructed using a constructor in an introduction rule. For instance, given two natural numbers n and m, an introducton rule for pairs
\frac {\Gamma \vdash n:\text {nat} \quad \Gamma \vdash m:\text {nat}} {\Gamma \vdash \langle n, m\rangle :\text {pair}(\text {nat}, \text {nat})}
might produce the introduction form \langle n, m\rangle . Evaluation of an introduction form produces a corresponding value in the semantic domain.

